ANTHAX - INDIA (10): (ODISHA) HUMAN
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 24 June, 2015
Source: The Indian Express [edited]
http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/Three-Die-of-Anthrax-in-One-Week/2015/06/24/article2883495.ece


3 persons died due to anthrax while 6 others were affected by the disease in Biriguda village under Laxmipur block of Koraput district in the last week.

The deceased are JK, SM, and RM [SM & RM have the same family name and may be related. - Mod.MHJ], As the disease [began affecting more people], the matter was reported to Laxmipur PHC and a medical team visited the village. The affected persons have been admitted to district headquarters hospital.

Medical officials from Laxmipur and Koraput on Tues 23 Jun 2015 distributed medicines among the villagers. The officials also shifted 6 affected persons to Koraput and Laxmipur hospitals.

ADMO, Public Health, Koraput, Arun Padhi said doctors are camping in the village and the condition of the affected persons is stable.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Koraput is one of the southernmost districts in Odisha and has figured in 10 posts in 2015 & 2014; see below for archive numbers. For a description of the district, go to: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Koraput.

Until the district veterinary service can get a handle on this zoonotic disease, the present situation will continue inflicting harm on both the human and livestock populations. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3461857,43530.]
